{
  "name": "RPlog_Tea_for...Three",
  "title": "Tea for...Three",
  "summary": "At her quaint beachside residence on Corellia, with her family already dispatched ahead to Ord Mantell, Ambassador Ambrosia Delgard receives an unexpected last-minute caller: Senator Dalek Rolynd of Ivaldi, secretly Prince Ivaldi, touring away from his homeworld. Over hastily brewed herbal tea, the two trade guarded diplomatic talk about the suspicious death of Senator Hastell, the worrying disconnect between the Senate and the Chief of State, and Rolynd's fear that Imperial hands lie behind Corellia's unrest. The decorum is shattered when CorSec Director Ewan Dain emerges from Ambrosia's refresher clad in only a pink towel, having taken a shower, leaving the flustered hostess scrambling to find him clothes. Once Dain is decently dressed, Ambrosia excuses herself to rejoin her family, lending her home and security detail so the Senator and the Director can confer over the spice cartel war ravaging Coronet and its possible ties to a looming Imperial move on Corellia.",
